            gameDescription: "Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney is a 2001 visual novel adventure game (originally for Game Boy Advance, later ported to DS, iOS, and modern platforms) where you play as rookie defense attorney Phoenix Wright taking on his first cases. You investigate crime scenes by examining objects and talking to witnesses, gather evidence into your Court Record, and then face off in dramatic courtroom trials where you cross-examine witnesses and present evidence to expose contradictions. A witness says they saw the defendant at 5 PM, but your autopsy report shows the victim died at 4 PM—slam your hand on the bench and shout 'OBJECTION!' Present the contradiction and watch testimonies crumble. Each case has five trial segments where you must find the truth: press witnesses for more details, present evidence that contradicts their statements, and piece together what really happened. Your mentor Mia Fey guides you, prosecutor Miles Edgeworth opposes you, and the judge presides over the chaos. Justice isn't just about punishment—it's about uncovering truth, defending the innocent, and ensuring the guilty face consequences for their actions.",
