                gameDescription: "Plants vs. Zombies is a 2009 tower defense game where you protect your house from waves of approaching zombies by strategically planting defensive flora in your lawn. Sunflowers generate sun energy, your only resource. Peashooters fire projectiles. Wall-nuts absorb damage. As levels progress, the threats multiply: Conehead Zombies with extra health, Pole Vaulting Zombies that leap your first defense, Football Zombies that charge through lines, Digger Zombies that tunnel behind your defenses, and the dreaded Zomboni that creates an ice trail of additional spawns. You have five lanes to defend, limited sun to spend, and the horde keeps coming. New plants unlock—Cherry Bombs for emergencies, Snow Peas to slow advances, Chompers for high-value targets—but so do new zombie variants. Night levels remove free sun. Pool levels add aquatic lanes. Roof levels change projectile physics. Your lawn is your territory, and every level is a test of resource management, strategic placement, and adapting your defense to whatever shambles toward your door. You're not giving up your home without a fight.",
                meaning: "You're under pressure and challenges are coming at you from multiple directions, but you must hold your ground. Like defending your lawn in Plants vs. Zombies, the Seven of Wands asks you to stand firm in your position even when others are trying to take what you've earned or challenge your authority. You have the high ground—don't give it up. This isn't about attacking; it's about defending what's yours with courage and determination. The opposition may seem endless, but you have the strength and resources to maintain your position. Stay vigilant, adapt to new challenges, and don't back down. You've earned your place—now protect it.",
