                gameDescription: "Devil May Cry 3: Dante's Awakening is a 2005 action game for PlayStation 2 that serves as a prequel, showing a younger, cockier Dante before he becomes the legendary demon hunter. The game opens with Dante in his not-yet-opened Devil May Cry office, eating pizza and reading a magazine, when a mysterious man named Arkham arrives with an invitation from Dante's brother Vergil. Dante's response? He charges shirtless out of his office and fights through hordes of demons with a grin on his face, spinning guns, juggling enemies in mid-air with sword combos, and taunting everything that tries to kill him. He doesn't ask questions or make plans—he just goes. Dante fights with pure improvisation and style, switching between weapons mid-combo (Rebellion sword, Ebony and Ivory guns, Cerberus nunchucks, Agni & Rudra dual swords), performing SSS-rank combos while making wisecracks, and treating life-or-death battles like performances. He surfs on enemies, rides rockets, fights his brother on top of a demonic tower because it sounds fun. Every encounter is approached with supreme confidence and zero hesitation. When asked if he has a plan, Dante's philosophy is simple: charge in, figure it out as he goes, and look good doing it. The Knight of Wands lives in Dante's entire approach: bold action over careful planning, passionate pursuit of whatever challenges come his way, charismatic confidence that borders on arrogance, reckless energy channeled into stylish combat, and the belief that instinct and flair will carry him through anything.",
