                keywords: "confidence • charisma • independence • passionate • magnetic personality • creative leadership • self-assured • inspiring • warmth • bold",
                gameDescription: "Bayonetta is a 2009 action game by PlatinumGames where you play as an Umbra Witch who awakens after 500 years with no memory of her past. From the moment she appears, Bayonetta commands every scene with absolute confidence and magnetic charisma. She fights angels with balletic grace, turning combat into a seductive dance of destruction—shooting with guns attached to her heels, summoning demons with her hair, dodging attacks with Witch Time that slows the world around her. Every movement is deliberate and stylish: she strikes poses mid-combo, blows kisses before executing finishing moves, and delivers one-liners with supreme self-assurance. Bayonetta never doubts her abilities, never asks for validation, and leads every encounter entirely on her own terms. She's independent to her core—working solo, making her own decisions, answering to no one. Her creativity in combat is unmatched: she summons demon limbs through portals, dances through bullet patterns, and improvises devastating combos with weapons ranging from swords to whips to ice skates. She inspires awe and fear in equal measure—angels flee from her, allies trust her completely, and even demons respect her power. The Queen of Wands lives in everything Bayonetta does: confident without arrogance, passionate about her craft, magnetic in presence, leading through demonstrated mastery and unapologetic self-assurance.",
